.:: Puzzle 2x4-Level-7-17::.
City: liverpool, san-francisco, paris, berlin
The people use 4 different means of transport: bike, jet-ski, quad-bike, train
1. the person traveling to san-francisco is somewhere between the person traveling to paris and the person traveling to liverpool##7
2. the person traveling to berlin is between the person driving the quad-bike and the person driving the train##2
3. the person traveling to paris is on the right of the person traveling to berlin##1
4. the person driving the jet-ski is somewhere to the left of the person driving the bike##5
5. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the left or right of the person traveling to liverpool##3
6. the person driving the train is on the far left or far right##3

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1    |     2     |  3   |    4     |
| City    | liverpool   | san-francisco  | berlin  | paris |
| Transport   | jet-ski | quad-bike | bike | train    |

